{{!--
  interface.hbs — rendered once per TypeSpec model as `public partial interface`.

  Override via tspconfig.yaml:
    options:
      "@massivescale/tsp-aspnetcore-api":
        templates:
          interface: "./templates/interface.hbs"

  ── Template variables ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  {{doc}}             — pre-rendered XML <summary> block (may be falsy)

  {{interfaceName}}   — interface name, e.g. "IUserProfile"

  {{baseInterface}}   — parent interface name when the model uses `extends`,
                        e.g. "IAnimal"; falsy when there is no parent

  {{baseClause}}      — ready-to-use inheritance clause including the leading
                        colon and space, e.g. " : IAnimal", or empty string.
                        Computed as: baseInterface ? ` : ${baseInterface}` : ""

  {{properties}}      — array of property objects in declaration order.
                        Each object has:
    .doc              —   pre-rendered XML <summary> block (may be falsy)
    .type             —   C# type string, e.g. "string?", "IList<Guid>?"
    .name             —   PascalCase property name
    .jsonName         —   camelCase JSON key for [JsonPropertyName], e.g. "firstName"
    .nullable         —   true when the type is nullable (ends with "?");
                          controls whether [JsonIgnore] is emitted

  {{propertiesBlock}} — shortcut: all properties pre-rendered (with JSON
                        attributes, without `public` access modifier) joined by
                        blank lines.  Pass through {{indent}} for 4-space
                        indentation inside the interface body.

  ── Built-in helpers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  {{indent <text>}}        — 4-space indent on every non-empty line
  {{#if (isDefined val)}}  — true when val is not undefined

  ── Handlebars #each data ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Inside {{#each properties}}:
    @index, @first, @last  — iteration metadata

  ── Common customisations ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  • Switch to get-only properties to enforce immutability:
      {{#each properties}}
          {{#if doc}}{{indent doc}}
          {{/if}}[JsonPropertyName("{{jsonName}}")]
          {{type}} {{name}} { get; }
      {{/each}}

  • Add a marker base interface (e.g. IEntity) to every generated interface:
      public partial interface {{interfaceName}} : IEntity{{baseClause}}

  • Remove `partial` if you don't need hand-written interface extensions.

  • Omit [JsonIgnore] and use a global JsonSerializerOptions:
      [JsonPropertyName("{{jsonName}}")]
      {{type}} {{name}} { get; set; }
--}}
{{#if doc}}{{doc}}
{{/if}}public partial interface {{interfaceName}}{{baseClause}}
{
{{#each properties}}{{#if doc}}{{indent doc}}
{{/if}}    [JsonPropertyName("{{jsonName}}")]
{{#if nullable}}    [JsonIgnore(Condition = JsonIgnoreCondition.WhenWritingNull)]
{{/if}}    {{type}} {{name}} { get; set; }
{{#unless @last}}

{{/unless}}{{/each}}
}
